        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 1:20PM EDT until June 8 at 2:15PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>SVRILM

The National Weather Service in Wilmington has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Pender County in southeastern North Carolina...
Eastern Bladen County in southeastern North Carolina...

* Until 215 PM EDT.

* At 120 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Lagoon, or 12
miles east of Elizabethtown, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Burgaw, Rowan, Penderlea, White Stocking, Wards Corner, Murray
Town, Lagoon, Willard, St. Helena, Atkinson, Watha, and Pender
Memorial Hospital.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please send your reports of hail and/or wind damage, including trees
or large limbs downed, by calling the National Weather Service office
in Wilmington at 1-800-697-3901.</instruction>
